MissionCommands.Message: Welcome to the Mercury-Redstone 3 historical mission. The cockpit is ready for full internal power and final checks.
[Follow the in-game steps to complete the final checks]
Automatic fuel is 95, manual is 96, cameras and tape recorders are running.
Back to Main, current is 29 amps [39 in this capsule].
Roger. Suit and cabin temperature, full CCW.
T/M blockhouse, do we have a go?
T/M blockhouse, do I have a go?
I got a no, I have to have a hold at two. [Roger, I am going to hold. 2 minutes and 40 seconds and holding.]
CTC, T/M is go. [Roger. Understand, T/M is go. We have a momentary hold. Stoney, hold line with me untill I give you the word. [Stoney, Rog.] Holding here, I have not recycled at this time.
Freedom 7, CAPCOM, radio check, how do you read?
7, reading you loud and clear CAPCOM, over to Chase.
[Ground discussions, wait for transmission to end.]
This is the CO, I did.
[Okay, ready to resume the count?] Roger. Ready to resume the count. STE, I am going to turn over the Stoney. Verify. ... Okay, Stoney, take it over. [Roger]
Freedom 7, Stoney, how do you read?
Ahh, Roger; lift-off and the clock is started.
Yes sir, reading you loud and clear.
This is Freedom 7. The fuel is go, 1.2g, cabin at 14 psi, oxygen is go.
This is Seven. Fuel is go, 1.8g, 8 psi cabin, and the oxygen is go.
Cabin pressure is holding at 5.5. Cabin holding at 5.5.
Fuel is go, 2.5g, cabin 5.5, oxygen is go ...
Rog, read you five by five, trajectory all okay.
Okay, it's a lot smoother now. A lot smoother.
Seven here. Fuel is go, 4g, 5.5 cabin, oxygen go, all systems are go.
That's all systems go, trajectory, all okay.
Periscope is coming out and the turn-around has started.
[Press ROGER when the turnaround is complete]
[Pitch down to -34 degrees, then up to -14 degrees]
[Yaw left 10 degrees, then return to original attitude of 0 roll, -14 pitch, 0 yaw]
Yaw is okay. Switching to manual roll.
[Roll left and right couple of degrees, then return to original attitude of 0 roll, -14 pitch, 0 yaw]
[Look into the periscope, use manual pitch to maneuver as you observe.]
On the periscope. What a beautiful view. Cloud cover over Florida. 3 to 4 tenths near the eastern coast. Obscures up to Hatteras. I can see Okeechobee. Identify Andros Island. Identify the Reefs.
Start retro-sequence. In retro-attitude are green.
[Manually attain retro attitude: pitch: -34, yaw: 0, roll: 0 (all should now be manual)]
Retro one, very smooth. Retro two. Retro three. All three retros are fired.
Roger. Do not have a light.
I do not have a light. I see the straps falling away. I heard a noise. I will use override.
Override used, the light is green.
I'm on Fly By Wire. Going to re-entry attitude. [Maneuver to reentry attitude: pitch: +34, roll: 0: yaw 0]
Switching to HF for radio check.
Freedom Seven, Cap Com how do read HF?
Ahh, Roger, reading you loud and clear HF, Deke. How me?
Freedom Seven, Cap Com. I didn't read your answer.
Ahh, Reading you loud and clear HF. How me?
[Okay. This is Freedom Seven. G build-up 3, 6, 9 .... Okay - Okay]
Cap Com, how do you read now?
Ahh, Roger, Deke, reading you loud and clear. How me?
The drogue is green at 21. The periscope is out. The drogue is out.
Okay at drogue deploy. I've got 70 percent auto, 90 percent manual. Oxygen is still okay.
And the snorkel's (out) at about 15,000 feet. Emergency flow rate is on. Standing by for main.
Main on green. Main chute is reefed. Main chute is green. Main chute is coming unreefed and it looks good. Main chute is good. Rate of descent is reading about 35 ft/sec.
Hello Cap Com. Freedom Seven. How do you read?
Hello CARDFILE 23, this is Freedom Seven. Do you read?
Freedom Seven this is Indian Cap Com, do you read me?
Affirmative Indian Cap Com, let me give you a report. I'm at 7,000 feet, the main chute is good, the landing bag is on green, my peroxide has dumped, my condition is good
Roger Freedom Seven, I understand you're at 7000 feet, your main chute is open, your [missing] is good, over.
Hello CARDFILE 23, CARDFILE 23, Freedom Seven. Over.
Freedom Seven, Freedom Seven this is CARDFILE 23, over.
Ahh, this is Seven. Relay back to Cap Com please. My altitude now 4,000 feet, condition as before, the main chute is good, the landing bag has deployed, the peroxide has dumped.
I'm about 1,500 feet now. The main chute still looks good. The rate of descent is indicating 30 ft/sec.
Freedom Seven, this is 23 I have no transmissions from Cape Cap Com, over.
Freedom Seven, this is Cape Capcom. Over.
Yeah, this is Seven, go ahead.
Negative. Just relaying my condition is still good. I'm getting ready for impact.
This completes the mission. Feel free to power down.

Title: MR-3: Freedom 7
Description:
The Mercury-Redstone 3 (Freedom 7) mission is the first U.S. space flight with the goals of testing attitude control modes, mans ability to operate in space and verify spacecraft systems.

Astronaut: Alan Shepard
BriefingText:
Mercury-Redstone 3: "Freedom 7"

Mission Objectives:
1. Familiarize man with a brief but complete space flight experience, including the lift-off, powered flight, weightless flight (approximately 5 minutes), re-entry, and landing phases of the flight.
2. Evaluate man's ability to perform as a functional unit during space flight by demonstrating manual control of spacecraft attitude before, during, and after retrofire and by use of voice communications during flight.
3. Study man's physiological reactions during space flight.
4. Recover the astronaut and spacecraft.

Flight Plan:
00:00 - Lift-off
01:24 - Pressure checks, max-q
02:22 - Launch Vehicle cutoff & tower sep
02:32 - Spacecraft sep and periscope deploy
02:37 - Turnaround
03:10 - Manual Control tests with ASCS
 Take manual control one axis at a time:
 A) Manual pitch, -14.5 to -34, then back to -14.5
 B) Manual yaw, left to -10, then back to 0
 C) Manual roll, left to -10, then back to 0

03:50 - Periscope visual observation in orbit attitude (-14 pitch, 0 yaw, 0 roll)
04:44 - Initiate retrofire sequence, return to retro fire attitude (-34 pitch, 0 yaw, 0 roll)
05:14 - Retrofire under manual control in all axes
06:14 - Retro jettison
06:15 - HF checks
06:20 - Reentry attitude using FBW (+34 pitch, 0 yaw, 0 roll)
06:44 - Periscope retroact (will happen with 0.05g in Reentry)
07:48 - Periscope retroact, 0.05g
08:20 - Max reentry accel.
09:38 - Drogue scope deploy
10:15 - Main chute deploy
15:22 - Landing (slightly offset in Reentry, tuning still)


Mission details:
Commander: Alan Shepard
Capsule name: Freedom-7
Booster: Redstone
Mission Profile: Sub-orbital

Planned launch time: May 5th 1961 07:20 AM EST
Countdown Start: May 4th 1961 ~8:30 PM EST
Capsule Ingress: May 5th 1961 05:15AM EST (06:15 EDT)
Unplanned delay at 07:05 EST for 1hr to let cloud cover clear and to fix a faulty power supply 
Shortly after countdown resume, further delays were caused by a system reboot at the Goddard Spaceflight center.

Mission start: 
T -15 minutes with final checks

Notes:
Reentry has desgined a generic capsule with all of the main Mercury features. Some readouts such as voltages, amps, trajectory details etc, might differ from audio. I have tried to recreate the mission to the best of my abilities within the limitation of my sim.

Have a good flight!
